### Which @angular/* package(s) are the source of the bug?

Don't known / other

### Is this a regression?

No

### Description

I am trying to extend an abstract class on `:host` selector and it works well until my abstract class has some nested selector styles.
Imagine this:
```scss
%test-hover {
  color: green;
  &:hover {
    color: gray;
  }
}

:host {
  @extend %test-hover;
}
```

It generates this:
```css
[_nghost-dxc-c100] {
  color: green;
}
```
But should generate this:
```css
[_nghost-dxc-c100] {
  color: green;
}
[_nghost-dxc-c100]:hover {
  color: gray;
}
```
However it works fine when the nested selector does not have `&`.
```scss
%test-hover {
  color: green;
  :hover {
    color: gray;
  }
}

:host {
  @extend %test-hover;
}
```
Produces this:
```css
[_nghost-gmj-c100] {
  color: green;
}
[_nghost-gmj-c100]   [_ngcontent-gmj-c100]:hover {
  color: gray;
}
```

I believe it should work for `:host` with `&` too.


